{
  "title": "Matrix Arithmetic",
  "summary": "Matrix equality, addition, scalar multiplication, and matrix multiplication — definitions, worked examples, and the transpose rule (AB)ᵀ = BᵀAᵀ.",
  "widget_type": "matrix_mult",
  "position": 2,
  "is_published": true,
  "content_html": "<style>\n.mat-wrap{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;vertical-align:middle}\n.mat{display:inline-grid;border-left:3px solid #94a3b8;border-right:3px solid #94a3b8;padding:6px 12px;gap:4px 16px;border-radius:2px;background:#1e293b}\n.mat td{text-align:right;font-family:monospace;font-size:.95em;color:#e2e8f0;min-width:24px}\n.mat-eq-block{background:#0f172a;border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:8px;padding:16px 20px;margin:12px 0;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;gap:12px}\n.mat-named{display:inline-flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:4px}\n.mat-label{font-size:.78em;color:#64748b;font-family:monospace}\n.op{font-size:1.3em;font-weight:700;color:#94a3b8}\n.eq{font-size:1.3em;font-weight:700;color:#38bdf8}\n.formula-box{background:#0f172a;border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 20px;margin:10px 0;font-family:monospace;font-size:1em;color:#f1f5f9;text-align:center}\n.dim-badge{display:inline-block;background:#1e3a5f;color:#7dd3fc;font-size:.82em;padding:3px 10px;border-radius:4px;font-family:monospace;margin:3px}\n.invalid-badge{background:#3b1f1f;color:#f87171}\n.note-box{background:#1a2e1a;border-left:4px solid #22c55e;border-radius:4px;padding:10px 16px;margin:10px 0;color:#bbf7d0;font-size:.93em}\n.def-box{background:#1e293b;border-left:4px solid #38bdf8;border-radius:4px;padding:10px 16px;margin:10px 0}\n.dim-diagram{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;font-family:monospace;font-size:.95em;margin:8px 0}\n.dim-box{background:#1e3a5f;color:#7dd3fc;padding:4px 12px;border-radius:4px}\n.dim-arrow{color:#94a3b8}\n.dim-result{background:#14532d;color:#86efac;padding:4px 12px;border-radius:4px}\n</style>\n<h3>1.2 Operations with Matrices</h3>\n\n<div class=\"def-box\">\n<strong>Definition 1.5 (Equality):</strong> Matrices A and B are equal if they have equal size and if their corresponding elements are equal — i.e., A = B if both are m×n and a<sub>ik</sub> = b<sub>ik</sub> for all i = 1,…,m and k = 1,…,n.\n</div>\n\n<h4>Matrix Addition</h4>\n<div class=\"def-box\">\n<strong>Definition 1.6:</strong> Let A and B be m×n matrices. The <strong>sum A + B</strong> is a new m×n matrix whose (i,k) entry is a<sub>ik</sub> + b<sub>ik</sub>.\n</div>\n\n<p><strong>Example 1.3:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\">\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>1</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>0</td><td>3</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">A</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"op\">+</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>−5</td><td>12</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>−7</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">B</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>1−5</td><td>2+12</td></tr><tr><td>0+1</td><td>3−7</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">element-wise</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>−4</td><td>14</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>−4</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">A + B</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"note-box\">Matrix addition is <strong>commutative</strong>: A + B = B + A<br>Matrix addition is <strong>associative</strong>: (A + B) + C = A + (B + C)</div>\n\n<h4>Scalar Multiplication</h4>\n<div class=\"def-box\">\n<strong>Definition 1.7:</strong> The <strong>product λA</strong> is obtained by multiplying every element of A by the scalar λ.\n</div>\n\n<p><strong>Example 1.4:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\">\n  <span class=\"op\">4 ×</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>5</td><td>−10</td></tr><tr><td>−7</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td>11</td><td>−18</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">A (3×2)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>20</td><td>−40</td></tr><tr><td>−28</td><td>12</td></tr><tr><td>44</td><td>−72</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">4A</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<p>The difference A − B = A + (−1)B. <strong>Example 1.6:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\">\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>1</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>0</td><td>3</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">A</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"op\">−</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>−5</td><td>12</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>−7</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">B</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>6</td><td>−10</td></tr><tr><td>−1</td><td>10</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">A − B</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Matrix Multiplication</h4>\n<div class=\"def-box\">\n<strong>Definition 1.8:</strong> Let A be m×n and B be n×p. The <strong>product AB</strong> is a new m×p matrix C = AB, whose (i,k) entry is:<br>\nc<sub>ik</sub> = a<sub>i1</sub>b<sub>1k</sub> + a<sub>i2</sub>b<sub>2k</sub> + … + a<sub>in</sub>b<sub>nk</sub> = Σ<sub>j=1..n</sub> a<sub>ij</sub>b<sub>jk</sub>\n</div>\n\n<p><strong>Dimension rule:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"dim-diagram\">\n  <div class=\"dim-box\">A (m × n)</div>\n  <span class=\"dim-arrow\">×</span>\n  <div class=\"dim-box\">B (n × p)</div>\n  <span class=\"dim-arrow\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"dim-result\">C (m × p)</div>\n  <span style=\"color:#94a3b8;font-size:.85em\">← inner dims must match</span>\n</div>\n\n<p><strong>Example 1.7:</strong> Row × Column</p>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\">\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>5</td><td>7</td><td>9</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">A (1×3)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"op\">×</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>6</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">B (3×1)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>5×2 + 7×4 + 9×6</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">step</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>92</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">AB (1×1)</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<p><strong>Example 1.8:</strong> Row × Matrix</p>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\">\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>5</td><td>7</td><td>9</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">A (1×3)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"op\">×</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>2</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>−3</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>1</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">B (3×2)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>92</td><td>−12</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">AB (1×2)</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"note-box\">BA does not exist here: (3×2)(1×3) — inner dims 2 ≠ 1. <strong>Generally AB ≠ BA.</strong></div>\n\n<p><strong>Example 1.9:</strong> Associativity — (CA)B = C(AB)</p>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\">\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>2</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>0</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>5</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">C (3×2)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"op\">×</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>−1</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>13</td><td>−3</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">A (2×2)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"op\">×</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>5</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>−1</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">B (2×2)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>70</td><td>17</td></tr><tr><td>168</td><td>87</td></tr><tr><td>287</td><td>139</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">CAB (3×2)</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"note-box\">Order of multiplication matters: CAB ≠ ACB or any other rearrangement.</div>\n\n<h4>Transpose of a Product</h4>\n<div class=\"formula-box\">(AB)<sup>T</sup> = B<sup>T</sup> A<sup>T</sup></div>\n\n<p><strong>Example 1.10:</strong> Verify (AB)<sup>T</sup> = B<sup>T</sup>A<sup>T</sup> for:</p>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\">\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>−1</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>−3</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">A (2×2)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"op\">,</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>5</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>−1</td></tr><tr><td>10</td><td>4</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">B<sup>T</sup> (3×2)</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"mat-eq-block\">\n  <span style=\"color:#94a3b8\">AB =</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>1</td><td>−4</td><td>−2</td></tr><tr><td>−4</td><td>5</td><td>−2</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">AB (2×3)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"op\">→</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>1</td><td>−4</td></tr><tr><td>−4</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td>−2</td><td>−2</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">(AB)<sup>T</sup> (3×2)</span>\n  </div>\n  <span class=\"eq\">=</span>\n  <div class=\"mat-named\">\n    <table class=\"mat\"><tr><td>1</td><td>−4</td></tr><tr><td>−4</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td>−2</td><td>−2</td></tr></table>\n    <span class=\"mat-label\">B<sup>T</sup>A<sup>T</sup> ✓</span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Compatibility Summary</h4>\n<div style=\"display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin:10px 0\">\n  <span class=\"dim-badge\">(2×3)(3×4) → valid → result 2×4</span>\n  <span class=\"dim-badge\">(1×3)(3×2) → valid → result 1×2</span>\n  <span class=\"dim-badge invalid-badge\">(2×3)(4×3) → INVALID</span>\n  <span class=\"dim-badge invalid-badge\">(3×2)(1×3) → INVALID</span>\n</div>\n",
  "exercises": [
    {
      "title": "Matrix equality",
      "prompt": "Matrices A and B are equal if:",
      "exercise_type": "multiple_choice",
      "options_json": [
        "They have equal size AND all corresponding elements are equal",
        "They have the same number of rows",
        "Their diagonals are equal",
        "They are both square"
      ],
      "answer": "They have equal size AND all corresponding elements are equal",
      "position": 1
    },
    {
      "title": "Compatibility check",
      "prompt": "Can you multiply a 2×3 matrix by a 3×5 matrix? What is the result size?",
      "exercise_type": "multiple_choice",
      "options_json": [
        "Yes, result is 2×5",
        "No, dimensions incompatible",
        "Yes, result is 3×3",
        "Yes, result is 2×3"
      ],
      "answer": "Yes, result is 2×5",
      "position": 2
    },
    {
      "title": "Commutativity",
      "prompt": "Is matrix multiplication commutative?",
      "exercise_type": "multiple_choice",
      "options_json": [
        "No, AB ≠ BA in general",
        "Yes, always",
        "Yes, for square matrices only",
        "Only for diagonal matrices"
      ],
      "answer": "No, AB ≠ BA in general",
      "position": 3
    },
    {
      "title": "Matrix product entry",
      "prompt": "For C = AB, the (i,k) entry c_ik is:",
      "exercise_type": "multiple_choice",
      "options_json": [
        "Σⱼ aᵢⱼ bⱼₖ (dot product of row i of A with column k of B)",
        "Sum of all entries in row i of A",
        "Product of diagonal entries",
        "aᵢₖ × bᵢₖ"
      ],
      "answer": "Σⱼ aᵢⱼ bⱼₖ (dot product of row i of A with column k of B)",
      "position": 4
    },
    {
      "title": "Transpose of product",
      "prompt": "(AB)ᵀ = ?",
      "exercise_type": "multiple_choice",
      "options_json": [
        "BᵀAᵀ",
        "AᵀBᵀ",
        "Aᵀ + Bᵀ",
        "(BA)ᵀ"
      ],
      "answer": "BᵀAᵀ",
      "position": 5
    },
    {
      "title": "Scalar multiply",
      "prompt": "4 × [[5,−10],[−7,3],[11,−18]] → entry at row 2, col 1 is:",
      "exercise_type": "multiple_choice",
      "options_json": [
        "−28",
